By BO Staff Writer The following statement was previously published on the Black First Land First website and is now reissued by Black Opinion: Black First Land First (BLF) is currently staging a peaceful sit-in at the offices of the Judicial Commission of Inquiry into State Capture (Zondo Commission) in Parktown. BLF is demanding the immediate suspension of the Secretary of the Zondo Commission, Dr Khotso de Wee. The sit-in is being conducted on the 3rd floor, Hillside House, 17 Empire Road, Parktown, Johannesburg. There will be a media update at 14h00 by one of the comrades in the sit-in. The sit-in will last until the Zondo Commission suspends Dr de Wee. #BLFSitin Issued by Black First Land First, National Coordinating Committee (BLF NCC) 18 January 2019 Black First Land First Email:blackfirstlandfirst@gmail.com Zanele Lwana
